• INGREDIENT A / INGREDIENT B = Combo-Drug, for example a pill that contains more than one active ingredient.
    INGREDIENT A - INGREDIENT B = Combo-Therapy, this is when multiple drugs start and end on the same date.
    INGREDIENT A + INGREDIENT B = Overlapping Therapy, this is when multiple drugs start on the same date but do not end on the same date, the drug to the right of the '+' symbol is the longer lasting drug.
